# Full Stack Production Audit & Remediation Checklist

## ðŸŽ¯ Objective
Achieve zero-defect production deployment with complete, tested functionality across all user journeys and application layers.

---

## 1. BUILD & CODE QUALITY

### 1.1 Syntax & Compilation
- [ ] All TypeScript files compile without errors
- [ ] No syntax errors in any source files
- [ ] All imports resolve correctly
- [ ] No circular dependencies detected
- [ ] Build process completes successfully
- [ ] Production bundle generates without warnings
- [ ] Source maps generate correctly (if enabled)

### 1.2 TypeScript Validation
- [ ] Zero TypeScript errors across entire codebase
- [ ] All `any` types documented with justification or replaced
- [ ] Strict mode enabled and passing
- [ ] All interfaces and types properly defined
- [ ] No implicit any declarations
- [ ] Generic types properly constrained
- [ ] Return types explicitly declared on all functions

### 1.3 Runtime Errors
- [ ] No console errors in development environment
- [ ] No console errors in production build
- [ ] All async operations have error handling
- [ ] Try-catch blocks implemented for critical operations
- [ ] Error boundaries implemented (React) or equivalent
- [ ] All promises properly handled (no unhandled rejections)
- [ ] Memory leaks tested and resolved

### 1.4 Linting & Code Standards
- [ ] ESLint passes with zero errors
- [ ] ESLint passes with zero warnings
- [ ] Prettier formatting applied consistently
- [ ] Custom lint rules passing (if applicable)
- [ ] Code complexity metrics within acceptable thresholds
- [ ] No commented-out code blocks in production files
- [ ] No TODO/FIXME comments in production code

---

## 2. DESIGN SYSTEM COMPLIANCE

### 2.1 Component Validation
- [ ] All components use design system tokens (colors, spacing, typography)
- [ ] No hardcoded color values outside design system
- [ ] No hardcoded spacing values outside design system
- [ ] Typography scales consistently applied
- [ ] All custom components documented in design system
- [ ] Component variants match design system specifications

### 2.2 Visual Consistency
- [ ] Design tokens match approved brand guidelines
- [ ] Responsive breakpoints consistently applied
- [ ] Grid system used correctly throughout
- [ ] Animation/transition timings match design system
- [ ] Z-index values follow established hierarchy
- [ ] Shadow/elevation values from design system only

### 2.3 Accessibility Compliance
- [ ] WCAG 2.1 AA minimum compliance achieved
- [ ] Color contrast ratios meet standards (4.5:1 text, 3:1 UI)
- [ ] Keyboard navigation fully functional
- [ ] Screen reader testing completed
- [ ] Focus indicators visible and consistent
- [ ] ARIA labels implemented correctly
- [ ] Semantic HTML structure validated

---

## 3. API & ROUTING ARCHITECTURE

### 3.1 Endpoint Completeness
- [ ] All planned API endpoints implemented
